  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nplease note that this is an issue tracker reserved for bug reports and feature requests.\r\n\r\nFor general questions please use the gitter channel or the Ethereum stack exchange at https://ethereum.stackexchange.com.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth version` - Geth/v1.8.2-stable/darwin-amd64/go1.10\r\nOS & Version: OSX\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nI expect to be able to by able to use Geth JS Console to unlock the account that I imported into Geth on the Ropsten network  \r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nI used Geth to connect to Ropsten so I can deploy a smart contract to it using an account that I imported.\r\n\r\nIn the Geth JS Console when I run the following after importing an account the following appears:\r\n\r\n```\r\n> eth.accounts\r\n[\"0xcdea3bfc82cbe46b8a7a8a648eda0969f145468b\"]\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut when I try to unlock it before deploying a smart contract to Ropsten, it shows the following error after I enter my passphrase `Error: The method personal_unlockAccount does not exist/is not available`:\r\n\r\n```\r\npersonal.unlockAccount(eth.accounts[0])\r\n```\r\nUnlock account 0xcdea3bfc82cbe46b8a7a8a648eda0969f145468b\r\nPassphrase: \r\nError: The method personal_unlockAccount does not exist/is not available\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nI was trying to deploy a smart contract by connecting Truffle to Geth. Below are the steps I followed to encounter the error `Error: The method personal_unlockAccount does not exist/is not available`. I was using Geth/v1.8.2-stable/darwin-amd64/go1.10, Truffle v4.0.6 (core: 4.0.6), Solidity v0.4.19 (solc-js)\r\n\r\n* Add to truffle.js file:\r\n\r\n```\r\nropsten: {\r\n  network_id: 3,\r\n  host: \"localhost\",\r\n  port: 8545,\r\n  gas: 2900000\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n* Open Terminal Window 1\r\n\r\n* reference: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/wiki/Managing-your-accounts\r\n* reference: https://ether.direct/2017/08/15/how-to-deploy-a-truffle-contract-to-ropsten/\r\n* reference: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/wiki/Command-Line-Options\r\n* in metamask click \"...\" icon next to account that want to use with\r\nropsten (i.e. 0xcdeA3bfc82CBe46B8a7A8A648eDA0969F145468b)\r\n* choose \"Export Private Key\"\r\n* choose \"Save As File\" (i.e. \"MetaMask RopTest1 Private Key.csv\")\r\n\r\n```\r\ntouch \"/Users/Ls/Downloads/MetaMask RopTest1 Password\";\r\nchmod 700 \"/Users/Ls/Downloads/MetaMask RopTest1 Password\";\r\ncat > \"/Users/Ls/Downloads/MetaMask RopTest1 Password\";\r\n> (((ENTER PASSWORD: testtest, then PRESS CTRL+D to exit)))\r\n\r\ngeth --testnet --networkid=3 account import \\\r\n  --password=\"/Users/Ls/Downloads/MetaMask RopTest1 Password\" \\\r\n  \"/Users/Ls/Downloads/MetaMask RopTest1 Private Key.csv\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n* show Ropsten testnet account list\r\n\r\n```\r\ngeth --testnet --networkid=3 account list\r\n\r\ngeth --testnet --networkid=3 \\\r\n  --rpc \\ --rpcaddr=\"localhost\" \\ --rpcport=8545 \\ --rpcapi=\"db,eth,net,web3,admin,personal\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n* Open Terminal Window 2\r\n\r\n```\r\ngeth attach http://127.0.0.1:8545\r\n\r\n> personal.unlockAccount(eth.accounts[1])\r\nUnlock account 0xcdea3bfc82cbe46b8a7a8a648eda0969f145468b\r\nPassphrase: \r\nError: The method personal_unlockAccount does not exist/is not available\r\n```\r\n\r\n* Open Terminal Window 3\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ truffle migrate  --network ropsten\r\nUsing network 'development'.\r\n\r\nRunning migration: 1_initial_migration.js\r\n  Replacing Migrations...\r\n  ... undefined\r\nError encountered, bailing. Network state unknown. Review successful transactions manually.\r\nError: authentication needed: password or unlock\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n",
